Hi,
 On a big screen lines of text get very long. Can we limit the width?

I'm not even on a 4k monitor, but on my 1920px wide monitor there fit ~270 characters per line in confluence (in edit mode, which is worst due to lacking sidebars).
 Recommended for readability are [50-60 characters per line|http://example.com/].

For people stumbeling over the same issue, here is some CSS you can paste into a browser extention like stylish to make it a bit more readable for yourself at least (effects editor and normal view):
{code:java}
.wiki-content:not(.comment){
    max-width:1008px;
    margin:auto !important;
}

.wiki-content p{
    max-width: 400px;
}
.wiki-content p img{
    height: auto;
}
.wiki-content li{
    width: 400px;
}
{code}

p2 CQ links are in the form 
{code:java}
 https://<hostname>/wiki/questions/<questionId>{code}
clicking it should show the question, but instead is page not found.

 

Workaround

adding something on to the end of the url fixes the redirect, eg
{code:java}
https://<hostname>/wiki/questions/<questionId>/something{code}
